               <p>JAMES WATMAN PHILPOTT. I am a <rs id="t18271206-242-viclabel1285" type="occupation">hatter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-242-victim1299 t18271206-242-viclabel1285"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18271206-242-crimeloc1286">Shadwell</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-242-crimeloc1286" type="placeName" value="Shadwell"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-242-crimeloc1286" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-242-off1283 t18271206-242-crimeloc1286"></join>. At twelve o'clock on Saturday night, I saw the prisoner talking together at my door: Burgess is in my employ, and was putting up the shutters - I saw Hughes go by - I went out, as if I was going away, and saw Hughes go and speak to Burgess, who gave him a hat - he and another boy walked away with it - I went between them, and tried to lay hold of both; they separated - I pursued Hughes, who dropped the hat, and ran into the watchman's arms - Burgess has lived three years with me; I would take him again.</p>
               <p>
            
